                  </hi>. I am a pawnbroker, These seven handkerchiefs, or six yards of silk, were pledged with me on the 26th of January, by the prisoner, for 9<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—he gave his name J. Jones, lodger, Alfred-street—we thought it was finished silk.</p>
